name: Hyperlink
description: Defines a hyperlink to webpages, files, email address, telephone numbers, SMS numbers, data URLs, or other URLs.

name: Abbreviation
description: Defines an abbreviation or an acronym, like HTML, CSS, or HTTP.

name: Address
description: Defines the contact information for the author/owner of a document or an article.

name: Image Map Area
description: Defines an area inside an image map.

name: Article
description: Defines a self-contained composition in a document, page, application, or site.

name: Aside
description: Defines a portion of a document whose content is only indirectly related to the document's main content.

name: Audio
description: Embeds sound content in documents.

name: Bold
description: Defines bold text to draw the reader's attention to the element's contents

name: Base
description: Specifies the base URL for all relative URLs in the document.

name: Bidirectional Isolation
description: Isolates a part of text that might be formatted in a different direction from other text outside it.

name: Bidirectional Text Override
description: Overrides the current directionality of text, so that the text within is rendered in a different direction.

name: Blockquote
description: Defines a section that is quoted from another source.

name: Body
description: Defines the document's body, or content.

name: Break
description: Produces a line break in text (carriage-return).

name: Button
description: Defines a clickable button.

name: Canvas
description: Used to draw graphics, on the fly, via scripting (usually JavaScript).

name: Caption
description: Defines the caption (or title) of a table.

name: Cite
description: Defines the title of a cited creative work (e.g. a book, a song, a movie, a TV show, a painting, a sculpture, etc.).

name: Code
description: Defines a short fragment of computer code.

name: Column
description: Defines a column within a table and is used for defining common semantics on all common cells.

name: Column Group
description: Defines a group of columns within a table.

name: Data
description: Adds a machine-readable translation of data into a more human-readable form.

name: Data List
description: Contains a set of <option> elements that represent the permissible or recommended options available to users.

name: Description Details
description: Provides the description, definition, or value for the preceding term in a description list.

name: Deleted Text
description: Defines text that has been deleted from a document.

name: Details
description: Defines additional details that the user can view or hide.

name: Definition
description: Indicates the term being defined within the context of a definition phrase or sentence.

name: Dialog
description: Represents a modal or non-modal dialog box or other interactive component, such as a dismissible alert, inspector, or subwindow.

name: Container
description: Defines a generic container for flow content, which does not inherently represent anything.

name: Description List
description: Defines a description list.

name: Description Term
description: Defines a term (or name) in a description list.

name: Emphasis
description: Defines emphasized text.

name: Embed
description: Embeds external content at the specified point in the document.

name: Field Set
description: Groups related elements in a form.

name: Figure Caption
description: Defines a caption or legend for a <figure> element.

name: Figure
description: Represents self-contained content, potentially with an optional caption, which is specified using the <figcaption> element.

name: Footer
description: Defines a footer for a document or section.

name: Form
description: Represents a document section containing interactive controls for submitting information.

name: Heading
description: Defines the highest-level heading for a section or subsection.

name: Heading
description: Defines the second-level heading for a section or subsection.

name: Heading
description: Defines the third-level heading for a section or subsection.

name: Heading
description: Defines the fourth-level heading for a section or subsection.

name: Heading
description: Defines the fifth-level heading for a section or subsection.

name: Heading
description: Defines the sixth-level heading for a section or subsection.

name: Head
description: Contains machine-readable information (metadata) about the document, like its title, scripts, and style sheets.

name: Header
description: Represents introductory content, typically a group of introductory or navigational aids.

name: Heading Group
description: Represents a heading and groups it with the content it's related to.

name: Horizontal Rule
description: Represents a thematic break between paragraph-level elements.

name: HTML
description: Represents the root (top-level element) of an HTML document, so it is also referred to as the root element.

name: Idiomatic Text
description: Represents a range of text that is set off from the normal text for some reason, like idiomatic text, technical terms, taxonomical designations, among others.

name: Iframe
description: Represents a nested browsing context, effectively embedding another HTML page into the current page.

name: Image
description: Embeds an image into the document.

name: Input
description: Represents an interactive control for web-based forms in order to accept data from the user.

name: Inserted Text
description: Represents a range of text that has been added to a document.

name: Keyboard Input
description: Represents user input, typically keyboard input.

name: Label
description: Represents a caption for an item in a user interface.

name: Legend
description: Represents a caption for the content of its parent fieldset.

name: List Item
description: Represents a list item.

name: Link
description: Specifies relationships between the current document and an external resource.

name: Main
description: Represents the dominant content of the body of a document.

name: Image Map
description: The map element is used with area elements to define an image map.

name: Mark Text
description: Represents text which is marked or highlighted for reference purposes.

name: Menu
description: Represents a semantic alternative to a list of items, for example, a list of commands.

name: Meta
description: Represents metadata that cannot be represented by other HTML meta-related elements.

name: Meter
description: Represents a scalar measurement within a known range, or a fractional value.

name: Navigation
description: Represents a section of a page that links to other pages or to parts within the page.

name: No Script
description: The noscript element defines a section of HTML to be inserted if a script type on the page is unsupported or if scripting is currently turned off in the browser.

name: Object
description: Represents an external resource, which can be treated as an image, a nested browsing context, or a resource to be handled by a plugin.

name: Ordered List
description: Represents an ordered list of items, typically rendered as a numbered list.

name: Option Group
description: Represents a group of options within a select element.

name: Option
description: Represents an option in a select element or as part of a list of suggestions in a datalist element.

name: Output
description: Represents a container for the result of a calculation or user action.

name: Paragraph
description: Represents a paragraph.

name: Picture
description: The picture element contains zero or more source elements and one img element to provide versions of an image for different display/device scenarios.

name: Preformatted Text
description: Represents preformatted text which is to be presented exactly as written in the HTML file.

name: Progress
description: Represents the completion progress of a task.

name: Quote
description: Represents a short inline quotation.

name: Ruby Parenthesis
description: Represents parentheses around a ruby annotation, used to display the parentheses in browsers that do not support ruby annotations.

name: Ruby Text
description: Represents the text of a ruby annotation, which is used to provide pronunciation, translation, or transliteration information for East Asian typography.

name: Ruby
description: Represents a ruby annotation, which is a small text attached to the main text to indicate pronunciation or meaning.

name: Strikethrough
description: Represents text that is no longer accurate or relevant.

name: Sample Output
description: Represents sample output from a computer program.

name: Script
description: The script element allows authors to include dynamic script and data blocks in their documents.

name: Search
description: Represents a control for searching through a document.

name: Section
description: Represents a generic standalone section of a document.

name: Select
description: Represents a control that provides a menu of options.

name: Slot
description: The slot element is a placeholder inside a web component that you can fill with your own markup.

name: Small
description: Represents side-comments and small print, like copyright and legal text, independent of its styled presentation.

name: Source
description: Specifies one or more media resources for the picture, audio, or video elements.

name: Span
description: The span element is a generic inline container for phrasing content.

name: Strong
description: Represents strong importance, seriousness, or urgency for its contents.

name: Style
description: The style element contains style information for a document, or part of a document.

name: Subscript
description: Represents a subscript.

name: Summary
description: Represents a summary, caption, or legend for the rest of the contents of the summary element's parent details element.

name: Superscript
description: Represents a superscript.

name: Table
description: Represents data in a two-dimensional table.

name: Table Body
description: The tbody element encapsulates a set of table rows (tr elements), indicating that they comprise the body of the table (table).

name: Table Data Cell
description: Represents a data cell in a table.

name: Template
description: The template element is a mechanism for holding client-side content that you don't want to be rendered when the page loads.

name: Text Area
description: Represents a multi-line plain-text editing control.

name: Table Foot
description: The tfoot element encapsulates a set of table rows (tr elements), indicating that they comprise the foot of the table (table).

name: Table Header Cell
description: Represents a header cell in a table.

name: Table Head
description: The thead element encapsulates a set of table rows (tr elements), indicating that they comprise the head of the table (table).

name: Time
description: Represents a specific period in time.

name: Title
description: The title element defines the document's title that is shown in a browser's title bar or a page's tab.

name: Table Row
description: The tr element defines a row of cells in a table.

name: Track
description: The track element is used as a child of the media elements audio and video. It lets you specify timed text tracks (or time-based data), for example to automatically handle subtitles.

name: Unarticulated Annotation
description: Represents a span of inline text which should be rendered in a way that indicates that it has a non-textual annotation.

name: Unordered List
description: Represents an unordered list of items, typically rendered as a bulleted list.

name: Variable
description: Represents a variable in a mathematical expression or a programming context.

name: Video
description: The video element is used to embed video content.

name: Word Break Opportunity
description: Represents a word break opportunity—a position within text where the browser may optionally break a line.
